data.content:
Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne	Tunisian Nationality
legal framework, nationality
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines the legal framework for Tunisian nationality.

Article 1	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
nationality definition, origin
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines individuals who have Tunisian nationality at birth as their nationality of origin.

Article 2	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
acquisition, loss, legal conditions
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that the conditions for acquiring and losing Tunisian nationality after birth are governed by the current law.

Article 3	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
retroactive laws, age of majority
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne applies new laws regarding Tunisian nationality to individuals born before the effective date of the laws, as long as they have not yet reached the age of majority.

Article 4	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
legal definition, adulthood
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines a person as an adult when they have reached the age of 18.

Article 5	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
territorial definition, Tunisian jurisdiction
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines the term 'in Tunisia' to include the entire Tunisian territory, territorial waters, and Tunisian boats, ships, and aircraft.

Article 6	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
parental nationality, child nationality
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne, which has been replaced, stated that a child is Tunisian if their father or mother is Tunisian.

Article 7	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
birthright nationality, generational nationality
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia, whose father and grandfather were also born in Tunisia, is considered Tunisian.

Article 8	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
stateless parents, residency requirement
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia to stateless parents who have resided in Tunisia for at least five years is considered Tunisian.

Article 9	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
unknown parents, birthright nationality
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia to unknown parents is considered Tunisian.

Article 10	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
foundling, birth presumption
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a newborn child found in Tunisia is presumed to have been born in Tunisia until proven otherwise.

Article 11	Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
birthright nationality, retroactive nationality
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child who is Tunisian under the provisions of this chapter is considered to have been Tunisian from birth, even if the conditions for Tunisian nationality are established after birth.

Article 33 is a specific article within the law that defines the acts that can lead to déchéance, which is the loss or deprivation of a right or status.

Article 34	délai
time frame, déchéance conditions
Article 34 specifies that déchéance is only incurred if the acts mentioned in Article 33 occur within a specific délai of ten years from the date of acquiring Tunisian nationality.

acquisition de la nationalité tunisienne	délai

The acquisition de la nationalité tunisienne must occur within a délai of ten years from the date of acquiring Tunisian nationality, as specified in Article 34.

Article 35	déchéance
extension of déchéance, family members
Article 35 allows for the extension of déchéance to the spouse and minor unmarried children of the individual, provided they have retained another foreign nationality.

déchéance	femme

La déchéance can be extended to the wife of the individual, but only if it is also extended to the children. This is specified in Article 35.

déchéance	enfants mineurs non mariés

revocation of naturalization, false declarations

Article 37	fausse déclaration
